/F1 13 Tf
(KAM Label Printing Guide) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
T*
(Version: 1.0) Tj
T*
(Prepared for: KAM \(KORT Asset Management System\)) Tj
T*
(Applies to: Thermal label printing with TSC printers \(including TSC 400 Pro\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
/F1 13 Tf
(1. Prerequisites) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
T*
(- Printer installed and visible in Windows Devices & Printers.) Tj
T*
(- Correct label media loaded \(for example, 50 x 25 mm\).) Tj
T*
(- Printer driver installed from TSC official package.) Tj
T*
(- KAM app updated with thermal-print label sizing changes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
/F1 13 Tf
(2. Configure Label Settings in KAM) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
T*
(Go to: Settings > Labels and Barcode.) Tj
T*
(Set Label Size to your media size \(50x25, 60x40, or 80x50\).) Tj
T*
(Set Print Margin \(mm\) according to your printer calibration \(usually 1 to 2 mm\).) Tj
T*
(Enable or disable Barcode and QR as needed.) Tj
T*
(Save changes.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
/F1 13 Tf
(3. Configure TSC 400 Pro in Windows) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
T*
(Open: Control Panel > Devices and Printers > TSC 400 Pro > Printing Preferences.) Tj
T*
(Set page/stock size exactly equal to your KAM label size.) Tj
T*
(Set orientation \(portrait/landscape\) to match label feed direction.) Tj
T*
(Set margins to minimum allowed by driver.) Tj
T*
(Disable scaling options in driver if available.) Tj
T*
(Run printer calibration from driver utility if labels shift.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
/F1 13 Tf
(4. Print Labels from KAM) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
T*
(Open an asset and click Print Label, or use bulk label printing.) Tj
T*
(In browser print dialog:) Tj
T*
(- Select printer: TSC 400 Pro) Tj
T*
(- Scale: 100% \(Actual Size\)) Tj
T*
(- Margins: None or Minimum) Tj
T*
(- Headers/Footers: Off) Tj
T*
(- Background graphics: Off \(unless required\)) Tj
T*
(Print a single test label first, then run bulk prints.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
/F1 13 Tf
(5. Server Commands After Deployment) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
T*
(Run these from the Laravel directory that contains the artisan file:) Tj
T*
(php artisan optimize:clear) Tj
T*
(php artisan view:cache) Tj
T*
(php artisan config:cache) Tj
T*
(php artisan route:cache) Tj
T*
(php artisan queue:restart) Tj
T*
(If route:cache fails because of Closure routes, use: php artisan route:clear) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
/F1 13 Tf
(6. Quick Troubleshooting) Tj
/F1 11 Tf
T*
(Issue: Could not open input file: artisan) Tj
T*
(Fix: cd into the correct Laravel directory, then run artisan commands.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Issue: Label prints too large/small) Tj
T*
(Fix: Ensure both Windows printer media size and KAM Label Size match exactly.) Tj
T*
() Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
